               <physDesc><p>This is so far the only attestation of a finite form of the root muḻu- used to indicate completion. (2) The expression yitu ariñcu anugrahikka vēṇṭiyatu seems to be a request of the scribe for a positive attitude towards himself. (3) In the date, vyā. is probably an abbreviation for viyāḻakkiḻamai, “Thursday” (which fits in with the other calendrical elements).</p></physDesc>
               
